Stefanini Group is hiring!
Open to W2 candidates only!
Do you want to be a part of a highly innovative, digitally transformative team and work on cutting edge, state of the art technologies? If yes, then this is for you! Exciting opportunity awaits, let us help you get started. For interested applicants, click the apply button or you may call: (248) 728-2611 / email: Laiza.Villapando@stefanini.com for faster processing. Thank you.
Looking for an IT Business Analyst. Open to any location that is in CST and EST time zones or where the candidate is willing to work EST hours/global hours as this role is in a global role.


Basic Qualifications:
Minimum Degree Required: High School Diploma
Minimum Years of Experience: 4 year(s) of progressive roles managing IT system/software development and project management processes.
Preferred Qualifications:
Degree Preferred: Bachelor Degree
Preferred Fields of Study: Information Technology, Computer Systems Analysis, Management Information Systems, Computer and Information Science
Certification(s) Preferred: Salesforce Certified Administrator, Tableau CRM & Einstein Discovery
Preferred Knowledge/Skills:
Demonstrates extensive abilities and/or a proven record of success in understanding business problems and developing Salesforce technology-enabled solutions that address the needs of large organizations, including the following areas:
Displaying familiarity of all phases of applications systems analysis and TCRM development;
Demonstrating the ability to effectively work and communicate with Business Analysts and Architects on requirements, implementation approaches and solutions;
Demonstrating the ability to assess the impact of new requirements on Salesforce.com end users across TCRM, including core technologies and processes, and all upstream and downstream connected applications and integrations;
Extracting relevant and meaningful information from multiple sources and applying it to solution designs that are scalable and supported by a well defined implementation approach;
Adapting to rapid changes and understanding the severity and impact of these changes in order to support and use future technology;
Demonstrating agility in modifying proposed solutions or approaches as needed to address evolving requirements;
Utilizing analytical, critical thinking and problem-solving skills; and,
Displaying attention to detail in executing and reviewing the work of others to establish quality standards that are achieved.
Demonstrates extensive abilities and/or a proven record of success in performing function and technical capabilities, and learning new capabilities, including the following areas:
Understanding and applying of TCRM best practices, functionality, setup & configuration and general architecture;
Articulating and clearly communicating complex problems and solutions in a simple, logical and impactful manner;
Demonstrating familiarity with TCRM Administration and Configuration (Hands on experience implementing datasets, recipes, workflow rules, validation rules, complex assignment rules, process builders, working with metadata etc.);
Creating and demoing working proofs of concept for business requirements using out of the box features of Salesforce TCRM;
Understanding third party integration and functionality and impact of these integrations, and ability to document an end-to-end process in the whole;
Understanding non-functional requirements related to access control, security, performance, or integrations; and,
Demonstrating the ability to consult and advise Developers when they have challenges in building a technical solution.
Demonstrates extensive abilities and/or a proven record of success as a team leader:
Contributing to a positive working environment by building relationships with team members;
Providing guidance, clarification, and feedback to less-experience team members; and,
Producing deliverables within a diverse, fast paced environment, collaborating effectively across teams and juggling multiple projects and initiatives in different phases simultaneously.

Alter Domus is currently seeking a new Business Analyst to join our Technology team at our Chicago, IL office.
JOB DESCRIPTION:
To ensure success as a technical business analyst, you should demonstrate experience and creativity in system development and application design. Outstanding technical business analysts combine their IT expertise with in-depth business knowledge.
Lead new business requirements for ongoing improvements to the Agency platform and client portal;
Responsible for supporting new solutions, data analysis, requirements;
Manage special projects and custom solutions for our clients;
Creation of process workflows and data diagrams;
Keep projects on budget and on time;
Present to management and propose solutions;
Apply technology skills to analyze and troubleshoot system issues; and
Oversee software testing and user acceptance testing.
YOUR PROFILE:
Bachelor’s degree in accounting, finance or engineering;
5+ years of Technical Business Analyst experience;
Proactive learning style, highly inquisitive and curious attitude, and excellent track-record of solving complex problems with focus and determination;
Familiar with Software Development Life Cycle;
Enjoys working with both business and technology professionals;
Highly capable of working both independently and collaboratively within a dynamic team environment;
Experience acting as a liaison or interface between business users and technology team is preferred;
Advanced knowledge of programming languages like SQL and data integration solutions;
Experience with business intelligence and data analytics a plus;
Advanced Excel skills a plus; and
Proficiency in Mandarin language another advantage.
ABOUT US:
Independent and possessing more than fifteen years’ experience in its field, Alter Domus has become a leader in corporate and management services for private equity & infrastructure and real estate funds as well as listed and unlisted companies. Our staff of over 2,000 people also provides fund administration and financial reporting services. We mentor and develop our employees’ technical knowledge and practical skills. We also champion commitment and a customer-oriented mindset.
WHAT WE OFFER:
Alter Domus offers a competitive, comprehensive benefits package including a generous vacation policy, a diverse work environment, and strong global connections. As you collaborate with colleagues in our fast-paced environment, you will gain exposure to demanding and stimulating experiences that you will take with you as your career progresses. We provide a sophisticated work environment with prominent clients that will take your ambitions and talents to the next level and give you the resources and support you need to succeed.
For more information, please visit: www.alterdomus.com.
Alter Domus is an Equal Opportunity Employer: All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability, or protected veteran status.
